ll,"body":"**Is your feature request related to a problem? Please describe.**\r\nWe want to avoid the issue we've seen where one of our dependencies update and consequently breaks `fonduer`. \r\n\r\n**Describe the solution you'd like**\r\nI'm imagining something like\r\n\r\n> If you're releasing a library on PyPI, you should declare whatever dependencies you know about, but not pin to a specific version. For example, if you know you need >= 1.2, but 1.4 is broken, then you can write something like somepkg >= 1.2, != 1.4. If one of the things you know is that somepkg follows SemVer, then you can add a < 2.\r\n\r\nBasically, something similar to [caret requirements](https://doc.rust-lang.org/cargo/reference/specifying-dependencies.html#caret-requirements) that are default in Rust (but we'll mainly care about major versions).\r\n\r\n**Describe alternatives you've considered**\r\nHaving ranges specified will be better than an exact pin, so we still benefit from updates in the dependencies, but can manually handle the API-breaking major changes.","closed_by":{"login":"lukehsiao","id":7573542,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjc1NzM1NDI=","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/7573542?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/lukehsiao","html_url":"https://github.com/lukehsiao","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/lukehsiao/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/lukehsiao/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/lukehsiao/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/lukehsiao/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/lukehsiao/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/lukehsiao/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/lukehsiao/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/lukehsiao/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/lukehsiao/received_events","type":"User","site_admin":false},"reactions":